metadata.title: Diamond DA42 Twin Star
aws::graph::propositions: Diamond DA42 Twin Star Military Operators
Switzerland's military procurement agency Armasuisse ordered 1 Diamond DA42 Twin Star.
The Diamond DA42 Twin Star ordered by Armasuisse was scheduled for delivery at the end of 2012.
The Royal Thai Air Force ordered 6 Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft.
The Royal Thai Air Force's Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft were scheduled for delivery in mid-2009.
The Turkmen Air Force operates 5 DA42MPP Guardian aircraft.
The DA42MPP Guardian is a variant of the Diamond DA42 Twin Star.
Ukraine's Border Guard Service operates three Diamond DA42 Twin Star planes.
Ukraine's Border Guard Service uses Diamond DA42 Twin Star planes for border patrol missions.
One Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft of Ukraine's Border Guard Service was lost in a 2012 accident.
The crew of the lost Diamond DA42 Twin Star was killed in the 2012 accident.
The 2012 accident involving Ukraine's Diamond DA42 Twin Star occurred in Zakarpattia.
The Royal Air Force operated 2 DA42MPP aircraft.
The Royal Air Force operated the DA42MPP aircraft in 2008 and 2009.
The Royal Air Force used the DA42MPP aircraft in a surveillance role.
The Bolivarian Military Aviation of Venezuela operates 6 Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft.
The Bolivarian Military Aviation uses Diamond DA42 Twin Star aircraft for training.
